TORAH METAPHYSICS - DISCUSSIONS OF CLASSICAL TORAH PHILOSOPHY AND THEOLOGY

Torah Metaphysics is an uncommon Jewish book that boldly reviews concepts in classical Torah philosophy, theology, and cosmology, based primarily on Talmudic, Medieval, and non-Kabbalistic Torah authorities.

Torah Metaphysics critiques Kabbalistic and materialist philosophies influencing the modern Jewish world.

Torah Metaphysics examines various controversial topics from a Torah perspective:
  • Hashem's Unity and Negative Theology
  • Unity of Torah and Science
  • Does the Zohar have a Valid Mesorah?
  • Chabad Replacement Theology
  • Problems with Chabad's Sefer Tanya
  • Evolution as an Atheist Religion
  • Intelligent Design Advances Judaism
  • The Age of the Universe
  • The Meaning of "Ein Od Milvado"
  • Reviving Classical Torah Theology

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.
